issue.title: Fix bug in Slice helper when dim value is zero

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Description**: 
We recently added clamping so that extremely large step values don't cause overflow/underflow on x86. That change overlooked handling dim_value of zero. Update so we don't clamp if dim_value is zero as that will set `step` to an invalid value.

**Motivation and Context**
#9465

body:
This model with random input hits a lot of operators with a shape that has a dimension value of zero. The 1.8.1 error is from the CUDA GatherND kernel. Fix for that was checked in a few months ago. 

https://github.com/microsoft/onnxruntime/commit/08eeb8763dd3aeaaa8b1bc31e9327d15d4849b33#diff-9213f372c794c937b337b32a0898b826d89262f8d2950d68e80c629d24632ba9

#9492 should fix the issue on master. I'm able to execute to the model successfully with that change.
Ok, I will build from source. I assume I go from the "Training" route of instructions in order to install onnxruntime-gpu?

The [inferencing build instructions](https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/build/inferencing.html) should be fine. 

e.g. something like this should build the onnxruntime-gpu python wheel in the ./build/Linux/RelWeithDebInfo/dist directory
`./build.sh --parallel --build_shared_lib --build_wheel --config=RelWithDebInfo --use_cuda --cuda_version=11.4`

I meet the same problem
while use`onnxruntime.InferenceSession(checkpoint_path, providers=["CPUExecutionProvider"])` it worked,
while use`onnxruntime.InferenceSession(checkpoint_path, providers=["CUDAExecutionProvider"])` Throwing the same error.
so I think not the .onnx file error.
If it's the same issue it should be fixed for both CPU and CUDA in the upcoming 1.10 release. That should be out in the next week or two, or you can build from source if you need something sooner.
